[1] Cholera: Benin (Borgou)
Date: Thu 9 Dec 2021
Source: Benin WebTV [in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://beninwebtv.com/2021/12/tchaourou-4-personnes-decedees-de-cholera-plusieurs-autres-cas-hospitalises/


A delicate situation in the village of Sebou, district of Sanson, in the town of Tchaourou, called out to the health authorities of the department of Collines. According to Deeman radio information from Parakou, 4 people died of cholera this Thu 9 Dec 2021, and several others were hospitalized.

According to information broadcast by Deeman radio in Parakou, the health authorities in the affected locality dispatched agents to the field to learn more about the situation and take urgent measures.

[Byline: Edouard Djogbenou]

