[3] Cholera: Congo DR (South Kivu)
Date: Wed 8 Dec 2021
Source: CGTN [edited]
https://africa.cgtn.com/2021/12/08/at-least-12-killed-in-worsening-cholera-outbreak-in-dr-congo/


More than 30 cases of cholera, including 12 deaths, have been recorded in less than 3 days in South Kivu province in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC). While speaking to reporters, the chief medical officer of the Kumbi Lulenge health zone, Cos Kenemo, said that the 1st case was recorded on Saturday [4 Dec 2021] and could have spread from the Miba village mining area. The outbreak has affected the Kumbi Lulenge health zone in Fizi territory.

Patients have been arriving at the hospital in critical condition, a situation that could be responsible for the high number of deaths, he said.

Kenemo advised residents to consume boiled drinking water and ensure proper food preparation, and he appealed for a cholera treatment center to be established in the area to contain the situation.

As of 17 Oct 2021, a total of 5950 suspected cholera cases, including 117 deaths, were reported in 79 health zones in 15 provinces in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, according to the European Center for Disease Prevention and Control.

